HEADWORD: Miserly
<hw>Mi"ser*ly</hw> <pr>(m⟦imac⟧"z⟦etil⟧r*l⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[From <er>Miser</er>.]</ety> <def>Like a miser; very covetous;
avaricious; stingy; sordid; niggardly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Avaricious; niggardly; sordid; parsimonious;
avaricious; penurious; covetous; stingy; mean. See
<er>Avaricious</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Misery</ent>⟦br⟧
